  <main class="container section">
    <h1>Join Us</h1>
    <p class="callout">
      We welcome motivated colleagues at all levels (students, research assistants, postdocs, and collaborators). 
      Our lab values inclusion, equity, and mentorship.
    </p>

    <h2>How to Apply</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Email a single PDF to <a href="mailto:divij.verma@university.edu">divij.verma@university.edu</a>
        with subject <strong>[Divij Verma Lab Application]</strong>.</li>
      <li>Include a brief cover letter (1–2 paragraphs), CV, and links to publications or code.</li>
      <li>State your preferred start date and whether you seek part-time or full-time roles.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What We Work On</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Clonal hematopoiesis & early myeloid disease (MDS/AML)</li>
      <li>Prostate cancer evolution, microenvironment & therapy response</li>
      <li>Environmental exposures, aging & inflammation in cancer risk</li>
      <li>Early detection, biomarkers & risk stratification</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Methods in the Lab</h2>
    <p>
      Primary human samples · in vivo models · CRISPR/Cas9 editing & lineage tracing · FACS · IHC/IF & microscopy ·
      library prep (single-cell & spatial) · targeted/bulk RNA-seq · quantitative analysis for validation.
    </p>
